-- London's Bow Bells House Is Sold by Japanese Owners for About $213 Million
-- Chris Bourke
-- 2010-07-09T09:59:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-09/london-s-bow-bells-house-is-sold-by-japanese-owners-for-about-213-million.html

          
          
             Bow Bells House, an office building
in London’s main financial district, was sold by its Japanese
owners for more than 140 million pounds ($213 million).  
 Mitsubishi Estate Co.  and  Mitsubishi Corp . sold the City of
London property to a private investor, according to a statement
today. The 165,000 square-foot (15,329 square-meter) building,
which also has some retail space, is leased to Bank of Ireland
and  Aberdeen Asset Management Plc .  
 The transaction will “enable us to undertake further U.K.
development,” Masami Amano, managing director of Mitsubishi
Estate’s U.K. business, said in the statement. “We are
currently looking across the City and West End for development
opportunities.”  
